_pdbx_entry_details.entry_id                   4CHA 
_pdbx_entry_details.compound_details           
;4CHA
THE ALPHA CHYMOTRYPSIN MOLECULE IS COMPRISED OF THREE        4CHA
POLYPEPTIDE CHAINS WHICH ARE DERIVED FROM THE ZYMOGEN OF     4CHA
THIS ENZYME BY EXCISION OF RESIDUES 14-15 AND 147-148. TO    4CHA
ASSIGN SEPARATE CHAIN IDENTIFIERS TO THE THREE CHAINS        4CHA
WOULD OBSCURE THIS RELATIONSHIP AND SO THIS WAS NOT DONE.    4CHA
CHAIN TERMINATOR RECORDS WERE INSERTED AFTER RESIDUES 146    4CHA
AND 245 TO INDICATE EXPLICIT TERMINI AND THE SPECIAL CODE    4CHA
EXC WAS USED IN THE SEQRES RECORDS TO DENOTE THE EXCISIONS.  4CHA
;
